# Brian Patrick Wcislo

> Apps That Move Business Forward

## About

Brian Patrick Wcislo is an independent app architect and operations builder with 23+ years of experience building digital products, campaigns, and interactive experiences. Based in Costa Rica. He builds custom apps, training platforms, and workflow systems — from first sketch to production-ready product.

He works with operations-driven businesses that are great at what they do and ready for systems that match their ambition. The common thread isn't company size — it's real complexity, real stakes, and teams ready to operate at the level they're capable of.

## Services

- **See the Full Picture**: Process mapping, opportunity identification, and path-to-build strategy.
- **Build the Thing**: From first sketch to production-ready app. Web or native. Fast and built to last.
- **Make it Fly**: Deploy, learn, evolve. Launch the app, unlock what's next.

## Selected Work

### ARS Flows
Custom operating system designed to power a fast-moving equipment services operation supporting one of the world's most recognized brands. Technicians, admins, and the owner each get a purpose-built experience — four guided workflows with 19 steps that move jobs from intake through invoicing with full visibility at every stage. Built in 9 weeks on React, TypeScript, and Supabase.
- 4 workflows, 19 guided steps
- 4 role-based dashboards
- 6-phase job lifecycle
- 3 distinct user roles
- 9-week initial build
- Phase 2 in progress

### GMAC Training Platform
Two-sided training platform that turns dense technical knowledge into tablet-first microlearning, interactive 3D tools, and gamified quizzes frontline teams genuinely engage with. Role-based dashboards give managers clear visibility from individual performance up through store, district, area, and region.
- 50% → 96% knowledge scores
- 99% manager approval
- 95% feel more supported
- 23,400+ modules completed
- 300,000+ videos consumed
- 580+ stores

### Mack Truck Builder
A touch-screen kiosk built for museum floors — where real truck engineering becomes something kids and families can play with. Visitors configure every system and drive what they built. 60+ unique combinations, a real-time physics game loop, and a live leaderboard — built for the Da Vinci Science Center in Allentown, PA.
- 5 step guided experience
- 60+ truck configurations
- 4 truck classes
- STEM content in 4 disciplines
- 60fps real-time physics
- 10,000+ engaged kids

### SoBo
SoBo is a friendship-safe lending app — a friendly middleman between the lend and the ask. Every loan gets its own negotiation thread, status tracking, and gentle nudge system. Built for the generous ones who know the quiet cost of stuff that never comes back. Available on iOS & Google Play via React Native and Supabase.
- iOS + Google Play
- 5 loan statuses tracked end-to-end
- 2-sided invite loop
- AI humor baked into every nudge
- Auto reminders sent for you
- Discover nearby items

